<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-185-834  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 185 834.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computers in Banking  April 1989 v6 n4 p30(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Document management systems: an integral part of a winningstrategy.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Marquardt, Leigh R.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Banks that accomplish the integration of data processing anddocument management systems are able to improve customer serviceefficiency and reduce front-end operating costs.andP;  An evolutionaryapproach, in which data, systems and loan processing managers workclosely with vendors, is a cost-effective alternative to expensiveand disruptive system replacement.andP;  The key is to bring thearchival component into the bank's data processing system.andP;  Retailcredit and the loan application process are particular areas wherepaperwork and overhead cost can be minimized to effect greaterinstitutional efficiency and customer satisfaction.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     BankingData ProcessingCost ReductionCustomer RelationsInformation Storage and RetrievalInformation Resources ManagementDocument Management Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>